manual_pairing_required.description:
The device at {address} failed to pair or authenticate. This commonly happens because stock ESPHome bluetooth_proxy does not handle passkey or numeric comparison requests (ESP_GAP_BLE_PASSKEY_REQ_EVT is not surfaced to Home Assistant).

Reason: {reason}

To fix this, open this integration's Reconfigure flow and follow the unpair/re-pair wizard. You will need to temporarily reflash the relevant ESPHome proxy into `ble_client` mode with `io_capability: keyboard_display` to complete pairing, then reflash it back to `bluetooth_proxy` mode.

